The paper deals with a multimodal search refinement method for fashion garments, which involves both visual and textual data. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of an attribute extraction module, which falls under the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a new training objective function and compares it with existing methods, which is related to Machine Learning (cs.LG).
